---
import { cx, css } from "@my-monorepo/ui-lib/css";

export type Props = Partial<Pick<HTMLDivElement, "className">>;

const { className } = Astro.props;
---

<div
  class={cx(
    className,
    css({
      backgroundColor: "teal.300",
      padding: "4",
      border: "1px solid token(colors.red.800)",
    }),
  )}
>
  <p class={css({ color: "purple.500", fontSize: "xs" })}>
    Using the `panda ship` command, we can generate a file that contains the
    extraction result (from your library component internal styles) so that you
    can include it as just another source of files to extract styles from.<br />
    <span class="some-text">
      You can try removing the
      `'./node_modules/@my-monorepo/some-component/dist/panda.json',` line from
      the `app/web/panda.config.ts` and see that the styles from this component
      will be missing.
    </span>
  </p>
  <slot />
</div>
